{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17563899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17563899"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:06:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:06:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16914"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16914"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.45,0.1,0.25,0.08,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9604"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108700"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9604"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16914"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91069"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1196"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"6356"},{"type":"tags","id":"11137"},{"type":"tags","id":"11148"},{"type":"tags","id":"11177"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"12218"},{"type":"tags","id":"12802"},{"type":"tags","id":"12962"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22672"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40354"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40374"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43666"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108700","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108700"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for contraceptive advice. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She reports regular but painful menstrual periods since menarche at age 13. She has never been pregnant.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. A pelvic ultrasound is arranged which suggests an unusual uterine configuration. Subsequent magnetic resonance imaging confirms a unicornuate uterus with a non-communicating rudimentary horn.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hysterosalpingogram","Laparoscopy","Renal tract ultrasound","Hormone profile","Chromosomal karyotype"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has been diagnosed with a unicornuate uterus, which is a type of M\u00fcllerian duct anomaly resulting from the incomplete development of one of the paramesonephric ducts during embryological development. Given the common embryological origin of the urinary and reproductive tracts, M\u00fcllerian anomalies are frequently associated with urinary tract abnormalities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is important to note that the entire renal tract would not have been visualised on a standard pelvic magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scan. A routine pelvic MRI is typically limited to the pelvis and may include the bladder and distal ureters, but it does not encompass the kidneys or the entire course of the ureters. Visualisation of the entire renal tract\u2014including the kidneys, ureters, and bladder\u2014requires further renal specific imaging.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERenal tract ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate next investigation as unicornuate uterus is associated with ipsilateral renal agenesis in up to 40% of cases. Early detection of renal anomalies is important for preventing complications and optimising future pregnancy care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHysterosalpingogram\u003C/strong\u003E would not add significant diagnostic information as MRI has already confirmed the diagnosis. Additionally, it would not detect associated renal anomalies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChromosomal karyotype\u003C/strong\u003E is not routinely indicated in isolated M\u00fcllerian duct anomalies unless there are other features suggesting a chromosomal disorder.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaparoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E might be considered if there is concern about endometriosis or if surgical management is planned, but it is not the next most appropriate investigation at this stage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHormone profile\u003C/strong\u003E would not provide useful information as M\u00fcllerian duct anomalies are structural developmental abnormalities and are not associated with hormonal disorders.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Unicornuate uterus is associated with ipsilateral renal agenesis in up to 40% of cases","Pelvic MRI is the gold standard imaging modality for diagnosing M\u00fcllerian duct anomalies","All patients with M\u00fcllerian duct anomalies should undergo renal tract imaging"],"references":["Jayaprakasan K, Ojha K. Diagnosis of Congenital Uterine Abnormalities: Practical Considerations. J Clin Med. 2022 Feb 25;11(5):1251. doi: 10.3390/jcm11051251. PMID: 35268343; PMCID: PMC8911320.","Akhtar MA, Saravelos SH, Li TC, Jayaprakasan K; on behalf of the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists. Reproductive implications and management of congenital uterine anomalies. Scientific Impact Paper No. 62. BJOG. 2019 Nov 20; DOI: 10.1111/1471-0528.15968."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91069"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16914"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"ty